------------------------------------------------------------------------
Proprietary integrations (build pipeline references; redistribution by
the upstream owner only):
------------------------------------------------------------------------

* NVIDIA Jetson Linux R36.5 (BSP, sample rootfs, public sources, toolchain)
  https://developer.nvidia.com/embedded/jetson-linux-r365
  Subject to the NVIDIA Software License Agreement bundled with each
  archive. This repo's scripts download these archives but do not
  redistribute them.

* Stereolabs ZED SDK + ZED X kernel driver
  https://www.stereolabs.com/developers/drivers
  Operators install per Stereolabs' end-user license. The kernel driver
  is shipped as compiled .deb by Stereolabs; building it under our
  PREEMPT_RT kernel requires source via your business agreement with
  Stereolabs.

* Axelera Voyager SDK (axelera-rt, axelera-devkit, axdevice)
  https://github.com/axelera-ai-hub/voyager-sdk
  Distributed under Axelera's terms via their PyPI repository.

* Rock7 RockBLOCK 9704 SDK
  https://github.com/rock7/RockBLOCK-9704
  See repo for license terms.

* Bootlin aarch64 toolchain (gcc 11.3 / glibc 2.36 / binutils 2.39)
  https://toolchains.bootlin.com/  (mirrored by NVIDIA at the L4T R36.5
  download page)
  GCC components GPL-3.0 with runtime exception; glibc LGPL-2.1+;
  binutils GPL-3.0. Used as a build-time toolchain only.

